%  Entries still marked "% PREPRINT ONLY" were CHECKED and confirmed to have NO
%  published version (DBLP lists them as CoRR / "Informal or Other Publication").
%  They are not oversights.
%
%  NB: NEVER write a literal at-sign inside a comment in this file. BibTeX does
%  not treat "%" as a comment character: it scans for at-signs and will read one
%  in a comment as the start of a new entry, then fail with
%  "I was expecting a `{' or a `('". Spell it out ("at-sign", "pass-at-k",
%  "an article entry") instead. This has bitten this file twice already.
%
%  NB2: escape underscores in "doi" fields as \_ (e.g. 10.1162/tacl\_a\_00638).
%  plainnat emits the DOI via \doi{...}, which typesets in TEXT mode, so a raw
%  underscore is read as a subscript and raises "Missing $ inserted" / "Double
%  subscript". This does NOT apply to "url" fields: plainnat wraps those in
%  \url{...}, which is verbatim-safe. Affects the ACL/MIT Press DOIs only.
% ============================================================================


